= Vote of no confidence called against leader of the opposition

In response to the TULF's attempt at a vote of no confidence against the government, the UNP put forward a counter vote of no condidence, this time against leader of the opposition A. Amirthalingam. This is unprecedented, and while normal custom dictates that opposition motions be given priority, the government overuled the TULF's motion and fast tracked their own VONC. 

The motion was supported by 36 UNP MP's and supported by the president himself though that may be dew to very few in the UNP daring to defy the party line.

On the day, as Amirthalingam stood to make his defense, the building went into chaos as UNP MP's began hurling a flood of choice epithets like “tiger supporter”, “liar”, and “traitor”. The MP from Panadura objected to Amirthalingam making a statment, speaker of parliament Bakeer Markar (UNP) agreed and refused to let Amirthalingam speak further. In response, TULF MP's stormed out of parliament.

- @against: SLFP MP Maitripala Senanayake raises a point of order, he points out that this sort of procedure is unprecedented not just in Sri Lanka, but the world, the motion was outside of parliaments power, the leader of opposition already enjoyed the confidence of the opposition and need not have the support of the government, and lastly even if the motion passed, there exists no procedures to replace Amirthalingam, he would still be leader of the opposition.
- @passive: SLFP MP's were unable to come up with anything subtstantive to say, this was incredibly unpopular for both the Left and Nationalists.

